cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper discusses the implementation of a surround view system for object detection and tracking, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks for object classification suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The tracking aspect of the algorithm may also fall under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of multiple fisheye images suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM).
